    <meta name=3D"description" content=3D"A Spanning Tree (ST) of a connect=
ed undirected weighted graph G is a subgraph of G that is a tree and connec=
ts (spans) all vertices of G. A graph G can have many STs (see this or this=
), each with different total weight (the sum of edge weights in the ST).A M=
in(imum) Spanning Tree (MST) of G is an ST of G that has the smallest total=
 weight among the various STs.">
