  <p>Then, Kruskal's algorithm will perform a loop through these sorted edg=
es (that already have non-decreasing weight property) and <b>greedily</b> t=
aking the next edge <b>e</b> if it does <b>not</b> create any cycle w.r.t. =
edges that have been taken earlier.</p><br><p>Without further ado, let's tr=
y <span class=3D"slide-actions">Kruskal</span> on the default example graph=
 (that has three edges with the same weight). Go through this animated exam=
ple first before continuing.</p>

