ous slide 4-4" style=3D"background-color: rgb(46, 187, 209);">=E2=86=90</di=
v>

  <div class=3D"electure-next" data-nextid=3D"4-6" title=3D"Go to the next =
slide 4-6" style=3D"background-color: rgb(46, 187, 209);">=E2=86=92</div>

  <div class=3D"electure-read-status" title=3D"Spend some more time reading=
 this slide">=F0=9F=95=91</div>
</div>
    <div id=3D"electure-4-6" class=3D"electure-dialog" style=3D"bottom:60px=
;left:50%;margin-left:-250px;width:500px;">
  <p>At the start of every loop, <b>T</b> is always part of MST.</p><br><p>=
If Kruskal's only add a legal edge <b>e</b> (that will not cause cycle w.r.=
t. the edges that have been taken earlier) with <b>min cost</b>, then we ca=
n be sure that <b>w(T U e) =E2=89=A4 w(T U any other unprocessed edge e' th=
at does not form cycle)</b> (by virtue that Kruskal's has sorted the edges,=
 so <b>w(e) =E2=89=A4 w(e')</b>).</p><br><p>Therefore, at the end of the lo=
op, the Spanning Tree <b>T</b> must have minimal overall weight <b>w(T)</b>=
, so <b>T</b> is the final MST.</p><br><p>On the default example, notice th=
at after taking the first 2 edges: 0-1 and 0-3, in that order, and ignoring=
 edge 1-3 as it will cause a cycle 0-1-3-0, we can safely take the next sma=
llest legal edge 0-2 (with weight 2) as taking any other legal edge (e.g., =
edge 2-3 with <b>larger</b> weight 3) will either create <b>another</b> MST=
 with equal weight (not in this example) or <b>another</b> ST that is not m=
inimum (which is this example).</p>

